{"key":"processedPost-10019483","value":{"id":10019483,"first":10018854,"last":10020014,"when":1237745958,"utime":"03/22/09 09:19 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />So can someone explain the idea of good vs. bad bacteria with relation to pasteurization using scientific fact in the explanation??? <br /></blockquote><br /><br />As shroomzey correctly said in his first post, it's not about bacteria, good or bad.&nbsp; Pasteurization of bulk substrates is not for the same purpose as pasteurization of milk.&nbsp; With bulk substrates, it's just to kill off the mold spores, to give our mushroom mycelium a chance to get a foothold on the substrate.<br /><br />Bacteria is generally not a contaminant of bulk substrates, and many species won't fruit at all if there is no bacteria present.<br />RR","title":"Re: Is PASTEURIZING really necessary???"}}